      "content": "Ah, it seems like your product title and image are having a little squabble on the mobile screen. The title is trying to claim more space than it has, causing it to overlap the image. Let's try to settle this dispute with some CSS adjustments.\n\nFirst, let's add a bit of padding to the product title to give it some breathing room. This will help prevent it from stepping on the image's toes:\n\n```css\n.product-title {\n  font-size: 24px;\n  margin-top: 10px;\n  padding-top: 10px; /* Add this line */\n}\n```\n\nNext, we can also add some padding to the product image to give it a bit more room to breathe:\n\n```css\n.product-image {\n  width: 100%;\n  height: auto;\n  padding-top: 10px; /* Add this line */\n}\n```\n\nWith these changes, your product title and image should be able to coexist peacefully on mobile screens. Happy shopping!",
